buh bom-bom-bom-bom ♪</i>

01:44.408 --> 01:46.715
I mean,
Ros is a cancer survivor.

01:46.715 --> 01:48.586
If we let go of her,
she'll lose her insurance.

01:48.586 --> 01:50.284
And Keith just adopted twins.

01:50.284 --> 01:52.155
I mean, that's a bad time
to be out of a job.

01:52.155 --> 01:54.114
I didn't mean
to get anybody fired.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.419
Who would you let go of?

01:55.419 --> 01:57.073
I mean, I have narrowed it down
to these four.

01:57.073 --> 01:58.466
- You want me to decide?
- Well, yeah.

01:58.466 --> 01:59.728
You want to be in management?

01:59.728 --> 02:01.730
Here's lesson 101:
making hard decisions.

02:01.730 --> 02:03.123
Well, our first lesson
was actually

02:03.123 --> 02:04.211
how to log into the web portal.

02:04.211 --> 02:05.386
It's, like,
needlessly complicated--

02:05.386 --> 02:07.562
Right.
I need this.

02:07.562 --> 02:08.563
Fine.

02:08.563 --> 02:10.913
If I had to choose, I guess...

02:10.913 --> 02:12.175
Syd.

02:12.175 --> 02:13.611
He has the worst numbers
and the most complaints.

02:13.611 --> 02:14.786
Yeah.
Sweet guy, though.

02:14.786 --> 02:15.961
I was hoping
you wouldn't pick him.

02:15.961 --> 02:17.137
Oh, I can pick somebody--

02:17.137 --> 02:18.616
No, you're right.
It has to be Syd.

02:18.616 --> 02:20.096
I just can't face him.
- Okay.

02:20.096 --> 02:21.576
Can you do it?

02:21.576 --> 02:22.533
Me?

02:22.533 --> 02:23.969
It'd hurt less
coming from you.

02:23.969 --> 02:25.623
These people think of me
as like a cool, younger sister

02:25.623 --> 02:28.496
or like an unobtainable crush.

02:28.496 --> 02:30.454
- Do they?
- Mm-hmm.

02:30.454 --> 02:32.021
Ah, there she is.

02:32.021 --> 02:34.850
Saint Dori saving the world
one mean comment at a time.

02:34.850 --> 02:36.112
Get away from me, Wesley.

02:36.112 --> 02:37.287
She's so perfect.

02:37.287 --> 02:38.810
She would never
spend company money

02:38.810 --> 02:39.898
going to a place where

02:39.898 --> 02:41.639
sexual mores
are temporarily lowered.

02:41.639 --> 02:44.773
- Because I don't need to.
- Okay, uh, Miss Pens.

02:44.773 --> 02:46.644
God, for someone who cares
so much about the company,

02:46.644 --> 02:48.211
you're pretty cavalier
with the pen usage.

02:48.211 --> 02:50.822
You got blue, black, red,
another blue.

02:50.822 --> 02:51.910
Must be nice.

02:51.910 --> 02:52.955
What does a pen cost?

02:52.955 --> 02:54.043
Like, what?
A dime?

02:54.043 --> 02:55.044
