lower our water bill

05:19.623 --> 05:21.625
if we put those little
push tabs on the sinks.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.061
You know, the one where
you gotta play whack-a-mole

05:23.061 --> 05:24.149
to, like, turn the water on?

05:24.149 --> 05:25.412
Oh, my God.
I hate those things.

05:25.412 --> 05:26.630
That's perfect.

05:26.630 --> 05:28.371
Oh, double-sided printing.

05:28.371 --> 05:29.807
We use half the paper,
not to mention

05:29.807 --> 05:31.853
freeing up filing space
and reducing trash.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.594
Okay, you're amazing at this.

05:33.594 --> 05:36.248
It's like "Good Will Hunting"
but, you know, like,

05:36.248 --> 05:37.772
a reboot with a Black woman,

05:37.772 --> 05:39.339
and I'd probably have to be gay
or British or something.

05:39.339 --> 05:40.470
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:40.470 --> 05:42.472
Joe America
shouldn't pay the tab

05:42.472 --> 05:44.387
for corporate America's
mistakes.

05:44.387 --> 05:45.606
Powerful, right?

05:45.606 --> 05:47.347
Very much so.
I felt it. Tingly.

05:47.347 --> 05:48.478
Ew.
Well, anyway.

05:48.478 --> 05:49.871
Hey, is what I'm wearing okay?

05:49.871 --> 05:50.828
When I got dressed
this morning,

05:50.828 --> 05:52.134
I didn't know I'd be doing TV.

05:52.134 --> 05:53.309
I think you look perfect,

05:53.309 --> 05:54.397
Especially given
the solemn news,

05:54.397 --> 05:56.312
it's good not to be
too polished.

05:56.312 --> 05:57.661
What do you mean
too polished?

05:57.661 --> 05:59.097
Do I look unpolished?
- No, I just mean real.

05:59.097 --> 06:00.490
You look real.

06:00.490 --> 06:02.057
So I don't look like
my normal supermodel self?

06:02.057 --> 06:03.363
It's been a stressful time lately

06:03.363 --> 06:04.451
in case you haven't noticed.

06:04.451 --> 06:05.843
Honestly?
Hey, you look beautiful.

06:05.843 --> 06:07.062
Really?
'Cause ten seconds ago,

06:07.062 --> 06:08.759
